Problem Statement: Concrete Strength Prediction¶

Objective:¶

To predict the concrete strength using the data available in file concrete_data.xls. Apply feature engineering and model tuning to obtain 80% to 95% of R2score.¶

In [43]:
X = conc1_df.drop('strength', axis=1)
y = conc1_df[['strength']]
In [46]:
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.30 , random_state=1)
In [121]:
from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression
from sklearn.linear_model import Ridge
from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsRegressor
from sklearn.gaussian_process import GaussianProcessRegressor
from sklearn import tree
from sklearn.metrics import recall_score, precision_score, roc_auc_score, accuracy_score
from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier
In [99]:
algo= []
tr = []
te = []

Linear Regression

In [100]:
regression_model = LinearRegression()
regression_model.fit(X_train, y_train)
algo.append('Logistic Regression')
tr.append(regression_model.score(X_train, y_train))
te.append(regression_model.score(X_test, y_test))

Ridge

In [128]:
r_model = Ridge()
r_model.fit(X_train, y_train)
algo.append('Ridge')
tr.append(r_model.score(X_train, y_train))
te.append(r_model.score(X_test, y_test))

KNeighborsRegressor

In [106]:

algo.append('KNeighborsRegressor')

te.append(l_model.score(X_test, y_test))

GaussianProcessRegressor

Parameter Tuning Using GridDSearch for KNeighborsRegressor and Decision Tree Regressor¶

from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV

parameters = {'n_neighbors': [5,7,9],
 'weights': ['uniform', 'distance'],
 'algorithm': ['ball_tree', 'kd_tree', 'brute'],
 'leaf_size': [20,30,40],
 'p'  :[1,2],
 'metric':['minkowski',2]}


clf = GridSearchCV(KNeighborsRegressor(), parameters, cv = 5, verbose = 2, n_jobs= 4)
